<div id="review_202587524" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/202587524" />
    <a title="Huw Evans" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6098128-huw-evans"><img alt="Huw Evans" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1314430789p2/6098128.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/202587524?book_show_action=true">Aug 26, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Huw Evans" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Huw Evans" href="/user/show/6098128-huw-evans">Huw Evans</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6098128-huw-evans?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6098128-huw-evans?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6098128-huw-evans?shelf=russian">russian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer202587524" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8902998079328210255">Ironically,I am writing this review on the 11th November. I have categorised it as fiction but there is a strong factual element - can I call it military faction? After Ivan Denisovich, the size of this book came as a surprise and the writing expands to fill the space between the covers, without lapse or hiatus. We remember our own war dead, but seem to have forgotten that the Russians lost twice as many men as did the UK. The appalling carnage at the beginning of the war is well described where</span>
  <span id="freeText8902998079328210255" style="display:none">Ironically,I am writing this review on the 11th November. I have categorised it as fiction but there is a strong factual element - can I call it military faction? After Ivan Denisovich, the size of this book came as a surprise and the writing expands to fill the space between the covers, without lapse or hiatus. We remember our own war dead, but seem to have forgotten that the Russians lost twice as many men as did the UK. The appalling carnage at the beginning of the war is well described where men without uniforms or weapons were thrown at a the opposition. In that fact alone lies much of the origin of the Russian revolution.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8902998079328210255" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
